<paper id="1595334710"><title>DPA attacks and s-boxes</title><year>2005</year><authors><author org="Oberthur Card Systems, Puteaux, France#TAB#" id="50202740">Emmanuel Prouff</author></authors><n_citation>107</n_citation><doc_type>Conference</doc_type><references><reference>1510418153</reference><reference>1524430769</reference><reference>1548656471</reference><reference>1557204831</reference><reference>1560093457</reference><reference>1562542037</reference><reference>1602453119</reference><reference>1606572167</reference><reference>1613874182</reference><reference>1629301835</reference><reference>1657240689</reference><reference>1670558497</reference><reference>1671031071</reference><reference>1897761346</reference><reference>1964723977</reference><reference>2090432705</reference><reference>2105114022</reference><reference>2106876320</reference><reference>2117877038</reference><reference>2148862943</reference><reference>2156817460</reference><reference>2234576048</reference><reference>2522062247</reference></references><venue id="2758283624" type="C">Fast Software Encryption</venue><doi>10.1007/11502760_29</doi><keywords><keyword weight="0.47717">Boolean function</keyword><keyword weight="0.42375">Discrete mathematics</keyword><keyword weight="0.49226">Block cipher</keyword><keyword weight="0.43036">Cryptography</keyword><keyword weight="0.41502">Linearity</keyword><keyword weight="0.41855">Algorithm</keyword><keyword weight="0.49199">Hamming distance</keyword><keyword weight="0.5037">Hamming weight</keyword><keyword weight="0.39562">Mathematics</keyword><keyword weight="0.0">Power consumption</keyword></keywords><publisher>Springer, Berlin, Heidelberg</publisher><abstract>For the power consumption model called Hamming weight model, we rewrite DPA attacks in terms of correlation coefficients between two Boolean functions. We exhibit properties of S-boxes (also called (n,m)-functions) relied on DPA attacks. We show that these properties are opposite to the non-linearity criterion and to the propagation criterion. To quantify the resistance of an S-box to DPA attacks, we introduce the notion of transparency order of an S-box and we study this new criterion with respect to the non-linearity and to the propagation criterion.</abstract></paper>